### Repro Steps & Context

`PhysicalPackageFile.GetStream()` returns a `Stream`, an `IDisposable`. It's not clear when/if that needs to be disposed.

https://github.com/NuGet/NuGet.Client/blob/dc2e3b27170c779e3c01a7306504fb83cb4ef147/src/NuGet.Core/NuGet.Packaging/PackageCreation/Authoring/PhysicalPackageFile.cs#L89-L106 says:

```csharp
        public Stream GetStream()
        {
            if (_streamFactory != null)
            {
                _lastWriteTime = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow;
                return _streamFactory();
            }
            else if (SourcePath != null)
            {
                _lastWriteTime = File.GetLastWriteTimeUtc(SourcePath);
                return File.OpenRead(SourcePath);
            }
            else
            {
                _lastWriteTime = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow;
                return MemoryStream;
            }
        }
```

If `GetStream()` returns a `FileStream`, it needs to be `Dispose()`d by the caller to avoid a resource leak. But if a `MemoryStream` is returned and the caller calls `Dispose()s`, it Disposes the internal `MemoryStream` which makes any further reads from it impossible.

